<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="133" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,335,1154,1180]" box="[189,335,1154,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,1154,1180]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1154,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1398,1201,1438]" box="[234,298,1201,1227]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1201,1227]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1398,1201,1438]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
ADULT HABITUS (
<figureCitation box="[385,561,1236,1263]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[223,1365,557,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-90@8.[189,1398,549,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 5. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov. A. ♂, holotype (HIST) habitus, dorsal view. B. ♀, paratype (HIST), habitus, dorsal view. C. ♂, holotype (HIST), head and pronotum, dorsal view. D. ♂, holotype (HIST), terga 3–9, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658627/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Figs 5A, C–D</figureCitation>
). General color dark brown to black (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1128,1236,1263]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[223,1365,557,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-90@8.[189,1398,549,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 5. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov. A. ♂, holotype (HIST) habitus, dorsal view. B. ♀, paratype (HIST), habitus, dorsal view. C. ♂, holotype (HIST), head and pronotum, dorsal view. D. ♂, holotype (HIST), terga 3–9, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658627/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Head mostly brown, with dark area around ocelli, tentorial callosities and M-line, the area sometimes extending to center of occiput. M-line dark brown. Triocellate, anterior ocellus slightly smaller. Antennae brown, scape darker, palpi brownish. Pronotum disc with dark brown rugosities and wide, brown, longititudinal stripe disjunct with thin black midline. Legs brown, femora darker. Wings hyaline, veins brown. Cerci brownish, apical segments darker.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1399,1477,1680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[319,420,1477,1504]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[223,1365,557,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-90@8.[189,1398,549,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 5. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov. A. ♂, holotype (HIST) habitus, dorsal view. B. ♀, paratype (HIST), habitus, dorsal view. C. ♂, holotype (HIST), head and pronotum, dorsal view. D. ♂, holotype (HIST), terga 3–9, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658627/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Figs 5D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[435,452,1477,1503]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[248,1358,305,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[219,1368,265,1853]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov., ♂, holotype (HIST). A. Terminalia, dorsal view. B. Terminalia, ventral view. C. Vesicle, ventral view. D. Vesicle, lateral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view. F. Tergum 10 and paraproct, dorsal view. G. Apex of tergum 10 and paraproct, lateral view (cercus removed). Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658629/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[468,540,1478,1504]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[266,1312,643,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-71@10.[236,1352,571,1890]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 7. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov., ♂, holotype (HIST). A. Tergum 10 and paraproct, dorsal view. B. Tergum 9, left portion, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658633/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">7A–B</figureCitation>
). Forewing length ca 
<quantity box="[808,904,1477,1504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="7.1">7.1 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length ca 6.0 mm. Abdominal tergal pattern obscure due to entirely black coloration. Tergum 9 bearing two patches of black sensilla on posterior margin by triangular medial membranous area extended anterolaterally forming a T-shaped paler marking. Tergum 10 with thin, longitudinal, pale, medial line; distal half bilobate, with 4–5 apical setae. Vesicle located on posterior margin of sternum 8, reduced to black transverse band. Paraprocts with recurved spiny apical sclerite, covered by ca. 13–14 tiny spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1398,1719,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
AEDEAGUS (
<figureCitation box="[323,394,1719,1745]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,379,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-12@11.[189,1398,359,1926]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov., ♂, holotype (HIST). A. Aedeagus, dorsal view. B. Aedeagus, ventral view. C. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658635/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Mostly membranous except for a dark ventrobasal sclerite, sclerite subquadrate with triangular postcentral notch; greatly enlarged posterior to ventrobasal sclerite. Aedeagus apical third upcurved and generally globular before narrowest nipple-like apex, brownish; mostly covered by fine spinules but lacking large spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[248,340,1890,1916]" box="[248,340,1890,1916]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[248,340,1890,1916]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1399,1933,1995]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
ADULT HABITUS (
<figureCitation box="[376,472,1933,1960]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[223,1365,557,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-90@8.[189,1398,549,1891]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 5. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov. A. ♂, holotype (HIST) habitus, dorsal view. B. ♀, paratype (HIST), habitus, dorsal view. C. ♂, holotype (HIST), head and pronotum, dorsal view. D. ♂, holotype (HIST), terga 3–9, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658627/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Figs 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[484,521,1933,1959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[215,1361,388,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-16@12.[189,1398,364,1891]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 9. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov., ♀, paratype (HIST). A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Abdomen, dorsal view. C. Subgenital plate, ventral view. D. Subgenital plate, lateral view. Abbreviations: see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658639/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">9A</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[743,887,1933,1960]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" metricValueMax="9.8" metricValueMin="7.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="8.8" valueMax="9.8" valueMin="7.8">7.8–9.8 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 5.8–8.0 mm (N=7). Body coloration generally similar to male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1400,265,432]" pageId="8" pageNumber="133">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[319,451,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[215,1361,388,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-16@12.[189,1398,364,1891]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 9. Tibetisoperla sclerotica sp. nov., ♀, paratype (HIST). A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Abdomen, dorsal view. C. Subgenital plate, ventral view. D. Subgenital plate, lateral view. Abbreviations: see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6658639/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="133">Fig. 9B–D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segments lighter and terga 1–8 with black medial tergal stripes in young individuals. Tergum 10 unmodified. Sternum 8 with sclerotized lateral portion and posterior subgenital plate, anteromedial portion membranous. Subgenital plate broadly triangular with dense long hairs, covering anterior third of sternum 9, with a posteromedial notch; lateral margins partially separated and heavily sclerotized. Sternum 9 with a pair of slope paramedial strips.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,375,471,498]" box="[189,375,471,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="133">EGG. Unknown.</paragraph>
