<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,304,377,403]" box="[189,304,377,403]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,377,403]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,377,403]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,423,520]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
The new species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Huo &amp; Du, 2021" authorityName="Huo &amp; Du" authorityYear="2021" box="[607,965,423,450]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Tibetisoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangluyui">
<emphasis box="[607,759,423,449]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">T. wangluyui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huo Q. B. &amp; Du Y. Z." box="[767,965,423,450]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" pagination="343 - 352" refId="ref3577" refString="Huo Q. B. &amp; Du Y. Z. 2021. A new genus of Isoperline (Plecoptera: Perlodidae) from Tibet, China. Zootaxa 4996 (2): 343 - 352. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4996.2.8" type="journal article" year="2021">
Huo &amp; Du, 
<quantity box="[906,965,423,449]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.13334" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" unit="in" value="2021.0">2021</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in dark body coloration and reduced vesicle on sternum 8, but it is easily separated from that species by the large ventrobasal sclerite of aedeagus which is entirely membranous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huo &amp; Du" authorityYear="2021" box="[696,848,493,519]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Tibetisoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangluyui">
<emphasis box="[696,848,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">T. wangluyui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
